claims:
Claims Claims 1. A method of determining homogeneity of a material mixture in a volume, the method comprising: receiving a first signal, from a first acoustic transducer at a first spatial position of the volume, indicative of an acoustic wave transmitted through the material mixture at the first spatial position of the volume; receiving a second signal, from a second acoustic transducer at a second spatial position of the volume, indicative of an acoustic wave transmitted through the material mixture at the second spatial position of the volume; and comparing the first and second signals to determine the homogeneity of the material mixture within the volume. 2. A method in accordance with claim 1 , wherein the method further comprises causing acoustic transducers to emit acoustic waves into the volume. 3. A method in accordance with claim 1 or claim 2, wherein comparing the first and second signals comprises using a statistical analysis. 4. A method in accordance with claim 3, wherein the statistical analysis comprises one or more of: a coefficient of variation comparison analysis; a correlation analysis; a cluster analysis; and a principal component analysis. 5. A method in accordance with any of the preceding claims, further comprising determining whether the homogeneity of the material mixture falls within an acceptable homogeneity threshold. 6. A method in accordance with claim 5, further comprising continuing a mixing process of the material mixture if the homogeneity of the material mixture falls outside of the acceptable homogeneity threshold. 7. The method in accordance with claim 5 or claim 6, further comprising dispensing the material mixture if the homogeneity of the material mixture falls within the acceptable homogeneity threshold. 8. A computer program comprising instructions which, when executed by a processor, cause a system incorporating the processor to carry out the method of any preceding claim. 9. A computer-readable medium comprising instructions which, when executed by a processor, cause a system incorporating the processor to carry out a method in accordance with any of claims 1 to 7. 10. A system for determining homogeneity of a material mixture in a volume, the system comprising: a volume for receiving the material mixture; a first acoustic transducer positioned adjacent the volume at a first spatial position, the first acoustic transducer being configured to produce a first signal indicative of an acoustic wave transmitted through the material mixture and received at the first acoustic transducer; a second acoustic transducer positioned adjacent the volume at a second spatial position, the second acoustic transducer being configured to produce a second signal indicative of an acoustic wave transmitted through the material mixture and received at the second acoustic transducer; and a processor configured to: receive the first and second signals from the first and second acoustic transducers, respectively; and compare the first and second signals to determine the homogeneity of the material mixture within the volume. 11. A system in accordance with claim 10, further comprising an array of acoustic transducers, the array of acoustic transducers comprising the first and second acoustic transducers, wherein each of the acoustic transducers is positioned adjacent the volume at a different spatial position of the volume and configured to: produce a signal indicative of an acoustic wave transmitted through the material mixture at a respective spatial position of the volume; and/or emit an acoustic wave into the material mixture. 12. A system in accordance with claim 11, wherein the processor is further configured to: 

 receive the signal from each acoustic transducer of the array of acoustic transducers; and compare the signals to determine the homogeneity of the material mixture within the volume. 13. A system in accordance with any of claims 10 to 12, wherein the processor is further configured to cause the first and second acoustic transducers to emit acoustic waves into the volume. 14. A system in accordance with any of claims 10 to 13, wherein the volume comprises one or more of: a mixing chamber; a conduit; and a mould. 15. A system in accordance with claim 14, wherein the volume comprises the conduit, the conduit being disposed between a mixing chamber and a mould. 16. A system in accordance with claim 14 or claim 15, wherein the volume comprises the conduit, and wherein the first and second acoustic transducers are located at different points along a length of the conduit. 17. A system in accordance with claim 14 or claim 15, wherein the volume comprises the conduit, wherein the first and second acoustic transducers are located at substantially the same point along a length of the conduit, and wherein the first acoustic transducer has a different orientation with respect to the second acoustic transducer. 18. A system in accordance with any of claims 11 to 17, wherein the processor is located remotely from the first and second acoustic transducers and the volume. 19. A kit of parts for determining the homogeneity of a material mixture in a volume, the kit of parts comprising: a first acoustic transducer configured to emit a first signal indicative of an acoustic wave transmitted through the material mixture at a first spatial position of the volume; 

 a second acoustic transducer configured to emit a second signal indicative of an acoustic wave transmitted through the material mixture at a second spatial position of the volume; and a processor connectable to the first and second acoustic transducers, the processor being configured to: receive the first and second signals; and compare the first and second signals to determine the homogeneity of the material mixture within the volume.
